## [FAIL] CRITICAL — A3f body-region removal ABSENT from Files-to-Change table

**What is missing:** The spec requirement A3f (marked CRITICAL in Sonnet R5) mandates removing the existing body-region `leadOnSlide`-check from `slide-template.tsx`:
```tsx
{slide.leadOnSlide && meta.lead ? (
  <LeadBlock lead={meta.lead} marginBottom={LEAD_TO_BODY_GAP} />
) : null}
```
This removal is described in the Requirements section (A3f) but is **completely absent from the Files-to-Change table**. The Files-to-Change table for `slide-template.tsx` lists items (a)–(e), all of which are additions/modifications. None says "remove the body-region leadOnSlide-check."

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:** A developer using Files-to-Change as their implementation checklist (standard workflow) will:
1. Add the new grid-cover branch with centered Title+Lead ✓  
2. Add centered TitleBlock+LeadBlock to the `isFirst && leadOnSlide===true` block ✓  
3. **NOT remove the body-region LeadBlock render** ✗  

Result: on no-grid-Slide-1 (`leadOnSlide: true`), Lead renders TWICE — once centered in the isFirst-block (A3d) and once left-aligned in the body-region. This was the exact bug A3f was added to prevent. No test directly covers double-render (E5 E2 verify presence, not absence of a second LeadBlock), so automated gates will not catch this during development. Only E5 visual smoke will catch it.

