## [FAIL] HIGH — Files-to-Change contradicts A3d: TitleBlock.marginBottom in no-grid-cover produces doubled gap

**What is missing / contradicted:**

- **Requirements (A3d):** `<TitleBlock marginBottom={meta.lead ? 0 : TITLE_TO_BODY_GAP} centered />`  
- **Files-to-Change item (e):** `<TitleBlock marginBottom={meta.lead ? TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP : TITLE_TO_BODY_GAP} centered />` annotated "(BEIDE existing conditionals UNCHANGED)"

The spacing rationale in A3d is explicit: "Title→Lead Gap = 18px. NICHT 36px doubled. Erreicht via TitleBlock.marginBottom=0 (wenn lead present) + LeadBlock.marginTop=TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP=18."

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:** Following Files-to-Change (the implementation guide), the developer keeps `marginBottom=TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP (18px)` on TitleBlock AND sets `marginTop=TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP (18px)` on LeadBlock → total Title→Lead gap = 36px instead of 18px. Visual regression on no-grid-Slide-1. E5 smoke ("No-Grid-Path") will catch it, but the implementation will be wrong coming out of the generator phase.

