## [FAIL] HIGH — Files-to-Change missing LeadBlock.marginBottom in no-grid-cover produces 0px Lead→Body gap

**What is missing:**

- **Requirements (A3d):** `<LeadBlock marginTop={TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP} marginBottom={LEAD_TO_BODY_GAP} centered />`  
- **Files-to-Change item (e):** `{meta.lead && <LeadBlock marginTop={TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP} centered />}` — **no `marginBottom` prop**.

A3d explicitly states: "Lead→Body Gap = 100px (LEAD_TO_BODY_GAP) — preserves pre-M4a behavior. Ohne marginBottom auf LeadBlock wäre der Gap 0px."

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:** Implementing from Files-to-Change, the developer omits `marginBottom={LEAD_TO_BODY_GAP}` on LeadBlock in the no-grid-cover branch. The Body region starts directly below Lead (0px gap instead of 100px). Visual regression on no-grid-Slide-1 items with lead text. E5 smoke will catch it, but since the existing body-region LeadBlock (A3f gap above) had `marginBottom={LEAD_TO_BODY_GAP}`, this is also a behavioral regression vs pre-M4a if A3f is correctly removed but (e) is followed literally.

