## [FAIL] HIGH — `const lead = meta.lead` in `buildManualSlides` becomes unused; TypeScript compile failure

**What is missing:** The Files-to-Change entry for `instagram-overrides.ts` specifies changes (a)–(c) which together remove ALL uses of the `lead` variable inside `buildManualSlides`:

- **Change (b):** `slideBudget` ternary no longer uses `lead` (was `lead ? Math.max(SLIDE_BUDGET - leadHeightPx(lead), 200) : SLIDE_BUDGET`)  
- **Change (c):** `leadOnSlide` field no longer uses `lead` (was `idx === 0 && hasGrid && Boolean(lead)`, becomes `!hasGrid && idx === 0`)

After both changes, `const lead = meta.lead;` at line 109 of `buildManualSlides` has zero references. TypeScript strict mode (`noUnusedLocals`) will produce a compile error. The spec does not say to remove this variable. The Code-Quality Gates require `pnpm exec tsc --noEmit` clean, so the build will fail.

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:** The developer will apply changes (a)–(c), run `tsc`, get `error TS6133: 'lead' is declared but its value is never read`, and must deduce on their own to remove the variable. The spec leaves this undefined. Depending on how they resolve it (remove variable vs suppress warning), they may introduce other issues.

*Same risk applies to `leadHeightPx` in both `instagram-post.ts` and `instagram-overrides.ts` — after removing `slide2BodyBudget` (A2b) and the manual-path budget reduction (also A2b), all call sites of `leadHeightPx` are removed. If `leadHeightPx` is not exported, TypeScript will flag it in `instagram-post.ts`. If it IS imported in `instagram-overrides.ts` but no longer called, the import line becomes unused. Spec says "bleibt verwendbar" but provides no disposition instruction.*

