## [FAIL] LOW — Defensive `gridImages` throw placement unspecified after isFirst split

**What is missing:** The existing `kind === "grid"` branch in `slide-template.tsx` opens with a defensive guard:
```tsx
if (!slide.gridImages || slide.gridImages.length === 0) {
  throw new Error(`[ig-export] kind="grid" slide ${slide.index} has empty gridImages...`);
}
```
This guard sits at the top of the unified `if (kind === "grid")` block. After A4b introduces separate `if (slide.kind === "grid" && slide.isFirst)` and `else if (slide.kind === "grid")` branches, the throw can no longer live in a shared prefix position (the two branches are separate conditionals).

The spec says pure-image slides are "UNCHANGED" but doesn't explicitly say where the guard moves. A developer may place it only in the cover sub-branch (cover-side `slide.gridImages ?? []` call handles null via empty-array) or accidentally drop it entirely for one of the two sub-branches.

