## [FAIL] LOW — A3e comment contradicts A3b: misleading "leadOnSlide:true only when lead non-empty"

**What is missing:** A3e states: "Im no-grid-cover-Branch ist Lead bei leadOnSlide===true per Definition non-empty (A2/A3 — leadOnSlide:true wird nur gesetzt wenn meta.lead non-empty wäre)."

This is factually incorrect. A3b explicitly sets `leadOnSlide: !hasGrid` unconditionally — regardless of whether `meta.lead` is non-empty. An item with no lead and no images gets `leadOnSlide: true` on its first slide. The spec RELIES on this being unconditional because `leadOnSlide === true` is the detection anchor for "this is no-grid-Slide-1" in the SlideTemplate.

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:** A developer reading A3e may add `&& Boolean(lead)` to the A3b rawSlides push, making it `leadOnSlide: !hasGrid && Boolean(meta.lead)`. This breaks the detection anchor for no-lead no-grid items (e.g., an agenda item with no lead text and no images). On such items, `leadOnSlide` would be `false` → detection condition never fires → Title is not centered. Partially covered by E5 "No-Grid + No-Lead-Path" visual smoke but NOT by automated tests (E2 tests specify "with lead" fixtures).

